Preheat broiler. Mix stuffing mix and hot water in medium bowl; cover. Let stand 5 min. Remove stems from mushrooms; chop stems. Cook and stir mushroom caps in 3 Tbsp. butter in large skillet until lightly browned. Arrange in shallow baking dish. Add stems and peppers to skillet; cook and stir until tender. Stir into stuffing. Spoon into mushroom caps; drizzle with 2 Tbsp. melted butter. Broil 5 to 7 inches from heat 5 min. or until heated through.